(1, 1, 'Big Five Safari', 'big-five-safari-', 'Big Five Safari Uganda |Tree-Climbing Lions & Rhino Tracking', 'Experience the ultimate Big 5 Safari in Uganda. Track Rhinos on foot at Ziwa, see the famous tree-climbing lions of Ishasha, and cruise the', 'book Uganda wildlife safari, Uganda safari deals, Uganda big five safari, cheap Queen Elizabeth tour, book Kidepo safari, private Kidepo game drive, Uganda walking safari tour, book Uganda photography safari, gorilla photography safari Uganda, Photography Safaris', 'Spot lions, elephants, buffalos, leopards, and rhinos in their natural habitat.', 'Embark on the Ultimate African Safari: Uganda’s Big Five & Beyond\r\nExperience the raw pulse of the wild with an extraordinary journey through Uganda’s most iconic landscapes, where the legendary Big Five await. Your adventure begins with an intimate, on-foot trek to encounter the majestic Southern White Rhinos at Ziwa Sanctuary, followed by a descent into the golden savannahs of Murchison Falls or Queen Elizabeth National Park. From the thrill of spotting tree-climbing lions and elusive leopards on sunrise game drives to the serenity of private boat cruises alongside massive herds of elephants and buffaloes at the water\'s edge, every moment is a masterpiece of nature. This isn\'t just a safari; it’s a soul-stirring immersion into the \"Pearl of Africa,\" perfectly blending high-octane wildlife encounters with the breathtaking beauty of thundering waterfalls and ancient craters.', '**The Daily Experience**\r\n- Sunrise Game Drives: Most days start before dawn (around 6:30 AM) to catch predators like lions and leopards while they are still active before the tropical heat sets in\r\n- On-Foot Rhino Tracking: A standout feature of a Ugandan Big Five safari is at the Ziwa Rhino Sanctuary, where you will leave the vehicle to track southern white rhinos on foot with expert rangers\r\n- The Search for Tree-Climbing Lions: In the Ishasha sector of Queen Elizabeth National Park, you\'ll look specifically for lions lounging in large fig trees a rare behavior nearly unique to this region\r\n\r\n\r\n**Logistics & Preparation**\r\n- Multi-Park Itineraries: Since rhinos are only found at Ziwa, a \"Complete Big Five\" trip usually requires a 3 to 5-day circuit covering Ziwa, Murchison Falls, and Queen Elizabeth National Park\r\n\r\n- Safari Vehicles: You will typically travel in a 4x4 safari Land Cruiser or van with a pop-up roof for 360-degree wildlife viewing\r\n\r\n- Best Time to Visit: The dry seasons (June–August and December–February) are best, as animals congregate around water holes and the vegetation is thinner, making them easier to spot.', '**The \"Big 5\" Icons of Uganda:**\r\n- Tree-Climbing Lions – Rare, world-famous behavior found in the Ishasha sector\r\n- Leopards of the Nile – Elusive masters of camouflage, often spotted in Murchison Falls\r\n- African Savanna Elephants – Massive herds found along the riverbanks and open plains.\r\n- Cape Buffalo – Powerful and iconic, often seen in groups of hundreds in Kidepo\r\n- Southern White Rhinos – Tracked on foot for a prehistoric-style encounter at Ziwa\r\n\r\n**Exclusive Ugandan  Big Five Safari Highlights**\r\n- On-Foot Rhino Tracking – One of the few places in Africa where you can safely walk within meters of Rhinos with expert rangers.\r\n\r\n- The Murchison Falls \"Squeeze\" – Seeing the world\'s most powerful waterfall where the Nile forces itself through a 7-meter gap.\r\n- Boat Safari Game Viewing – Viewing elephants, buffalo, and hippos from the water on the Victoria Nile or Kazinga Channel.\r\n\r\n**Top Big 5 Safari Locations:**\r\n- Murchison Falls National Park – Best for Lions, Leopards, Elephants, and the mighty Falls\r\n- Queen Elizabeth National Park – Famous for Tree-Climbing Lions and the Kazinga Channel boat cruise.\r\n- Ziwa Rhino Sanctuary – The exclusive home for Rhino tracking in Uganda.\r\n- Kidepo Valley National Park – A remote \"True Wild\" experience with massive Buffalo herds and Lions.\r\n- Lake Mburo National Park – Great for Leopards and Buffalo (though no Lions or Elephants here).', '[\"Guided Rhino Trekking on foot at Ziwa Sanctuary.\",\"A scenic boat launch cruise on the Victoria Nile or Kazinga Channel.\",\"Transportation\",\"Professional Guide\\/ Driver\",\"Accommodation:\",\"Park Access: All National Park entrance fees\"]', '[\"Travel Insurance\",\"Tourist Visa\",\"International and domestic flights\",\"Optional Primate Trekking: Permits for Gorilla Trekking ($800) or Chimpanzee Tracking ($200) unless specifically added to your itinerary.\"]', '[\"Trekking poles\",\"Head torch \\/ flashlight\",\"First aid kit\",\"Binoculars\",\"Walking stick\",null]', NULL, NULL, '[\"Neutral-Colored Layers: Pack lightweight, breathable clothes in khaki, green, or tan. Avoid bright colors (which distract animals) and dark blue or black (which attract tsetse flies)\",\"Sturdy Walking Shoes: Comfortable, closed-toe shoes or light hiking boots for the Rhino Trekking and nature walks.\",\"Personal Binoculars: While the guide has a pair, having your own (8x42 is ideal) ensures you don\'t miss a second of the action.\",\"Camera with Zoom Lens: A lens of at least 300mm is recommended for capturing those stunning \\\"Big Five\\\" close-ups.\",\"Yellow Fever Certificate: A mandatory requirement for entry into Uganda.\",null]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'moderate', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', 'activities/icons/f0MHrabaGnSBT3hIXnanoFUZxNSoHEOeWssC6BuQ.jpg', 'activities/fs0Sc01o2FvlSrV7J7gcRMkOJDs8NYn7wBFM4WjG.jpg', 'activities/featured/kbwxVbGcJ51rp28lLAVX1nXTfJiM3ATVvIyTXASq.jpg', 1, 1, 1, '2026-02-07 14:36:55', '2026-04-04 16:04:56', NULL),
