(26, 4, NULL, NULL, 'Lake Kivu', 'lake-kivu', 'Beautiful lake with resort towns and beaches.', '{\"overview\":[],\"activities\":[],\"wildlife\":[],\"geography\":[],\"practical\":[],\"accommodation\":[],\"extras\":[]}', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/featured/pD3aEBF6xRyUuoNYJUiSsEBAHf6pBSafecNRZS4g.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'km²', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/6fbndqdRTgV1Imk7X3rYARm8nK2xmGDalTrjbaIr.jpg', 0, 0, 5, '2026-02-07 14:36:57', '2026-03-21 23:39:02', NULL, '2026-03-04 04:49:57'),
(27, 3, NULL, 'National Park', 'Kidepo Valley National Park', 'kidepo-valley-national-park', 'Kidepo Valley National Park is a remote and beautiful wilderness in northeastern Uganda, known for its vast savannah plains, rugged mountains, rich wildlife, and peaceful uncrowded safari experience.', '{\"overview\":[{\"id\":\"blk-92d4fcce-637e-4c08-8c98-ad4b8df34a0b\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo Valley National Park is Uganda\\u2019s most remote and wild national park, located in the rugged semi-arid valleys of northeastern Uganda near the borders of South Sudan and Kenya. Spanning about 1,442 square kilometers, the park is celebrated for its dramatic landscapes of rolling savannah plains, rocky outcrops, distant mountain ranges, and seasonal rivers that create a truly untouched African wilderness.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-27700a11-070c-48d9-a0cf-a110027d4b51\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Often described as one of Africa\\u2019s most spectacular hidden gems, Kidepo offers an authentic safari experience far from crowds, where vast open spaces stretch endlessly and wildlife roams freely across the golden plains. The park\\u2019s isolation has preserved its raw beauty, giving visitors a rare feeling of exploration and discovery.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-76df6662-1a8b-41f3-ada8-7e68f1751280\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo is especially famous for hosting wildlife species not commonly found in other Ugandan parks, making it a unique destination for adventurous travelers. Combined with breathtaking sunsets, rich cultural encounters with the Karamojong people, and a peaceful atmosphere, the park delivers a powerful sense of connection to nature and Africa\\u2019s wild heritage.\"}],\"activities\":[{\"id\":\"blk-06c614fc-2662-4811-a96e-859565ed3bd7\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-car]] Game Drives\"},{\"id\":\"blk-46cab6b0-e543-48bc-ab27-73c03ae302a3\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Guided game drives take you across the park\\u2019s wide golden plains where wildlife roams freely. Visitors can watch lions resting under acacia trees, elephants moving in herds, giraffes feeding on treetops, and zebras grazing peacefully, offering a true feeling of Africa\\u2019s untouched wildernes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-cb92ed95-4fa0-4222-bfe0-055d584fee35\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Nature Walks\"},{\"id\":\"blk-82f19e29-ca0f-45f0-bfe8-4f6af76c08e4\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Walking safaris allow visitors to experience the park more closely and quietly. With an armed ranger guide, you explore the savannah on foot, observe animal tracks, discover unique plants, and enjoy the natural sounds of birds and wildlife around you.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-90c86c1a-b3f6-498f-9969-f9b874d0dc42\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-hiking]]  Mountain Hiking\"},{\"id\":\"blk-54513ffd-1d0a-41d8-b977-5bb05b239a5e\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Visitors can hike scenic mountain areas such as the slopes of Mount Morungole, enjoying fresh air and breathtaking panoramic views of valleys, rivers, and endless plains stretching into the horizon.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-434a18cf-a449-4a68-90ae-1c894592ce69\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-dove]] Bird Watching\"},{\"id\":\"blk-c093bc4d-1ada-402d-9362-8a1ce4dabf1b\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo is home to many bird species, including rare and migratory birds. Bird lovers can spot colorful species in grasslands, riverbanks, and woodlands while enjoying the peaceful natural environment.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-bdbc9778-8918-439d-84ca-10f6699fdc16\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-users]] Cultural Visits\"},{\"id\":\"blk-6e0b184c-95f1-4620-ab59-91daac26cfbf\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tourists can visit the nearby Karamojong communities to learn about their traditional pastoral lifestyle, unique manyatta homesteads, traditional dances, handmade crafts, and strong cultural heritage.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-833e1035-44f8-410e-91ab-d3fc62c21ade\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-camera]] Photography Safaris\"},{\"id\":\"blk-b0e1e9be-c83d-4e08-9d43-4dbeffeef71b\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The park\\u2019s dramatic scenery, clear skies, and abundant wildlife provide perfect opportunities for photography. Visitors can capture stunning images of animals in their natural habitat, beautiful landscapes, and memorable African sunsets.\"}],\"wildlife\":[{\"id\":\"blk-405e7239-d78c-4c4f-bab9-43a41f41e50a\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Elephants\"},{\"id\":\"blk-62668fed-d806-43d1-8459-8b0069a58370\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Large herds of African elephants roam the park\\u2019s vast plains and valleys. They are often seen moving in family groups, grazing calmly or cooling off near seasonal rivers. Their size, strength, and gentle social behavior make them one of the most admired animals during safaris.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-66a15cf1-e6be-47fe-9eb2-f84dfcb88d61\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Lions\"},{\"id\":\"blk-e9ce2ae1-a9fb-48cd-8a10-91a5579eb817\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo is home to powerful lions that dominate the open savannah. They are commonly spotted resting under trees during the day or hunting in the cooler hours. Hearing their deep roars echo across the valley is a thrilling reminder of the wild nature of the park.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-e5341f5b-2581-4d08-aae2-30fe82455b81\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Leopards\"},{\"id\":\"blk-7b3b82c0-c490-4261-abf4-5e32b4f4faaf\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"These solitary and secretive cats are among the park\\u2019s most elusive predators. Leopards prefer rocky areas and woodlands where they quietly stalk prey. Spotting one resting in a tree or moving silently through tall grass is a rare and exciting safari moment.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-3d5afddc-73f5-4e68-9d27-c662e1ea194f\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Giraffes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-e15a51a3-7018-47c4-8e21-d45224916a0b\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo is famous for its tall Rothschild\\u2019s giraffes, easily recognized by their long necks and beautiful patch patterns. They gracefully move across the plains feeding on treetop leaves, adding elegance and beauty to the park\\u2019s scenery.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-de8e27d6-be16-43bf-a851-3934c6e736ab\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Cheetahs\"},{\"id\":\"blk-4c634a83-c168-4995-83d2-f920acbad6b1\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo is one of the few places in Uganda where cheetahs can be found. These slender and incredibly fast predators prefer open grasslands where they use speed rather than strength to hunt prey. Seeing one in the wild is a rare privilege.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-b2ecbaa1-9aac-42be-9f52-e66e2ec73733\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-dove]]  Birds\"},{\"id\":\"blk-f6944798-a0ef-4b22-97cc-44ad23cb9bab\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo hosts over 470 bird species, making it a rewarding destination for bird lovers. Large ostriches roam the plains while eagles, hornbills, and colorful migratory birds fill the skies and trees with life and sound.\"}],\"geography\":[{\"id\":\"blk-02b65269-8a3c-43d3-aa2e-c96bc407158a\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kidepo Valley National Park is defined by its dramatic and rugged natural scenery that makes it one of Africa\\u2019s most spectacular wilderness areas. The park lies within a semi-arid region characterized by vast open savannah plains that stretch endlessly toward the horizon, giving visitors a powerful sense of space and isolation.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-f31d4f72-dcc7-4690-8fef-052f8601056b\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The landscape is surrounded by distant mountain ranges and rocky hills that form a stunning backdrop to the golden grasslands. Seasonal rivers such as the Kidepo and Narus Rivers cut through the park, creating lifelines that attract wildlife, especially during the dry season when animals gather around remaining water sources.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-66a0026f-ede1-4313-89d5-3e1698fe5523\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Scattered across the plains are rocky outcrops and kopjes that provide resting spots for predators and panoramic viewpoints for visitors. During the rainy season, parts of the park transform as short grasses turn green and wildflowers bloom, adding fresh beauty to the already striking terrain.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-80aab92e-94b7-44f7-a7b3-46194fcfef22\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The combination of sweeping valleys, dry riverbeds, rolling plains, and rugged highlands creates a raw and untouched wilderness that feels far removed from modern civilization, offering one of the most authentic and scenic safari environments in Africa.\"}],\"practical\":[],\"accommodation\":[],\"extras\":[]}', 0, 'Kidepo Valley National Park is Uganda’s most remote and wild national park, located in the rugged semi-arid valleys of northeastern Uganda near the borders of South Sudan and Kenya. Spanning about 1,442 square kilometers, the park is celebrated for its dramatic landscapes of rolling savannah plains, rocky outcrops, distant mountain ranges, and seasonal rivers that create a truly untouched African wilderness.\r\n\r\nOften described as one of Africa’s most spectacular hidden gems, Kidepo offers an authentic safari experience far from crowds, where vast open spaces stretch endlessly and wildlife roams freely across the golden plains. The park’s isolation has preserved its raw beauty, giving visitors a rare feeling of exploration and discovery.\r\n\r\nKidepo is especially famous for hosting wildlife species not commonly found in other Ugandan parks, making it a unique destination for adventurous travelers. Combined with breathtaking sunsets, rich cultural encounters with the Karamojong people, and a peaceful atmosphere, the park delivers a powerful sense of connection to nature and Africa’s wild heritage.', '## [[icon:fas fa-car]] Game Drives\r\n\r\nGuided game drives take you across the park’s wide golden plains where wildlife roams freely. Visitors can watch lions resting under acacia trees, elephants moving in herds, giraffes feeding on treetops, and zebras grazing peacefully, offering a true feeling of Africa’s untouched wildernes\r\n\r\n## Nature Walks\r\n\r\nWalking safaris allow visitors to experience the park more closely and quietly. With an armed ranger guide, you explore the savannah on foot, observe animal tracks, discover unique plants, and enjoy the natural sounds of birds and wildlife around you.\r\n\r\n## [[icon:fas fa-hiking]]  Mountain Hiking\r\n\r\nVisitors can hike scenic mountain areas such as the slopes of Mount Morungole, enjoying fresh air and breathtaking panoramic views of valleys, rivers, and endless plains stretching into the horizon.\r\n\r\n## [[icon:fas fa-dove]] Bird Watching\r\n\r\nKidepo is home to many bird species, including rare and migratory birds. Bird lovers can spot colorful species in grasslands, riverbanks, and woodlands while enjoying the peaceful natural environment.\r\n\r\n## [[icon:fas fa-users]] Cultural Visits\r\n\r\nTourists can visit the nearby Karamojong communities to learn about their traditional pastoral lifestyle, unique manyatta homesteads, traditional dances, handmade crafts, and strong cultural heritage.\r\n\r\n## [[icon:fas fa-camera]] Photography Safaris\r\n\r\nThe park’s dramatic scenery, clear skies, and abundant wildlife provide perfect opportunities for photography. Visitors can capture stunning images of animals in their natural habitat, beautiful landscapes, and memorable African sunsets.', '## Elephants\r\n\r\nLarge herds of African elephants roam the park’s vast plains and valleys. They are often seen moving in family groups, grazing calmly or cooling off near seasonal rivers. Their size, strength, and gentle social behavior make them one of the most admired animals during safaris.\r\n\r\n## Lions\r\n\r\nKidepo is home to powerful lions that dominate the open savannah. They are commonly spotted resting under trees during the day or hunting in the cooler hours. Hearing their deep roars echo across the valley is a thrilling reminder of the wild nature of the park.\r\n\r\n## Leopards\r\n\r\nThese solitary and secretive cats are among the park’s most elusive predators. Leopards prefer rocky areas and woodlands where they quietly stalk prey. Spotting one resting in a tree or moving silently through tall grass is a rare and exciting safari moment.\r\n\r\n## Giraffes\r\n\r\nKidepo is famous for its tall Rothschild’s giraffes, easily recognized by their long necks and beautiful patch patterns. They gracefully move across the plains feeding on treetop leaves, adding elegance and beauty to the park’s scenery.\r\n\r\n## Cheetahs\r\n\r\nKidepo is one of the few places in Uganda where cheetahs can be found. These slender and incredibly fast predators prefer open grasslands where they use speed rather than strength to hunt prey. Seeing one in the wild is a rare privilege.\r\n\r\n## [[icon:fas fa-dove]]  Birds\r\n\r\nKidepo hosts over 470 bird species, making it a rewarding destination for bird lovers. Large ostriches roam the plains while eagles, hornbills, and colorful migratory birds fill the skies and trees with life and sound.', 'Kidepo Valley National Park is defined by its dramatic and rugged natural scenery that makes it one of Africa’s most spectacular wilderness areas. The park lies within a semi-arid region characterized by vast open savannah plains that stretch endlessly toward the horizon, giving visitors a powerful sense of space and isolation.\r\n\r\nThe landscape is surrounded by distant mountain ranges and rocky hills that form a stunning backdrop to the golden grasslands. Seasonal rivers such as the Kidepo and Narus Rivers cut through the park, creating lifelines that attract wildlife, especially during the dry season when animals gather around remaining water sources.\r\n\r\nScattered across the plains are rocky outcrops and kopjes that provide resting spots for predators and panoramic viewpoints for visitors. During the rainy season, parts of the park transform as short grasses turn green and wildflowers bloom, adding fresh beauty to the already striking terrain.\r\n\r\nThe combination of sweeping valleys, dry riverbeds, rolling plains, and rugged highlands creates a raw and untouched wilderness that feels far removed from modern civilization, offering one of the most authentic and scenic safari environments in Africa.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kidepo Valley National Park Safaris | Uganda’s True Wilderne', 'Discover Kidepo Valley National Park in northeastern Uganda, a remote wilderness known for vast savannah plains, dramatic mountains, rare wildlife species, and', 'Kidepo Valley National Park, Kidepo safaris, Uganda safari parks, wildlife safaris Uganda, remote national parks Africa, Kidepo wildlife, Uganda adventure travel, African savannah safari, Kidepo tour packages, Uganda tourism, Africa safari', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/featured/9gKPmwbvzJ3lMHQ4xUwANVdrO1i5n5PNQ8X2ThEn.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'km²', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, 5, '2026-02-09 05:27:43', '2026-03-11 21:40:21', NULL, '2026-03-11 21:40:21');
INSERT INTO `destinations` (`id`, `country_id`, `region`, `type`, `name`, `slug`, `description`, `sections_content`, `is_draft`, `detailed_overview`, `what_to_see_do`, `wildlife_highlights`, `geography_landscape`, `best_time_visit`, `how_to_get_there`, `accommodation_options`, `practical_information`, `cultural_significance`, `photography_tips`, `nearby_attractions`, `interesting_facts`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `meta_keywords`, `overview_images`, `activities_images`, `wildlife_images`, `landscape_images`, `accommodation_images`, `gallery_images`, `featured_image`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `area_size`, `area_unit`, `altitude_min`, `altitude_max`, `entry_fee_foreign`, `entry_fee_resident`, `entry_fee_local`, `currency`, `established_year`, `annual_visitors`, `phone`, `email`, `website`, `opening_hours`, `best_season`, `climate`, `avg_temp_high`, `avg_temp_low`, `rainfall_annual`, `image`, `is_popular`, `is_active`, `sort_order`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `draft_user_id`, `published_at`) VALUES
(28, 3, NULL, 'National Park', 'Lake Mburo National  Park', 'lake-mburo-national-park', 'Lake Mburo National Park is one of Uganda’s most accessible and unique wildlife destinations, located in western Uganda between Kampala and Mbarara. It is especially popular for short safaris, weekend trips, and travelers who want a quieter, less crowded park experience.', '{\"overview\":[{\"id\":\"blk-d6d697f8-e72c-4df0-9185-c726b73e2fbf\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lake Mburo National Park is one of Uganda\\u2019s smallest but most diverse savannah parks, known for its rich wildlife, scenic landscapes, and wide range of visitor activities. It offers a compact yet rewarding safari experience and is especially suitable for short trips, stopovers, and travelers who want close wildlife encounters without long travel times.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-0eac5c76-fef3-41b3-b91f-90ef3ffd20c9\",\"type\":\"image\",\"media_id\":19,\"block_id\":\"blk-0eac5c76-fef3-41b3-b91f-90ef3ffd20c9\",\"caption\":\"\"}],\"activities\":[{\"id\":\"blk-217ea0cd-4a2a-422b-8c8d-6e32759b8eed\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Game Drives\"},{\"id\":\"blk-12ac4276-f71f-4592-9f0c-f46e9fbb64d9\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Morning, afternoon, and night drives\"},{\"id\":\"blk-f90349df-f3ce-426e-a87e-410c6c57fd96\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good road network for viewing zebras and antelopes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-d5c662a9-a73f-44ec-b074-2a2f44f433ee\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Night drives allow chances to see nocturnal animals\"},{\"id\":\"blk-d0f4fd81-c3a3-492c-8b0b-85add36fc389\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Boat Safaris\"},{\"id\":\"blk-e97a15c5-8aab-4267-bf32-ed96bcc78a16\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conducted on Lake Mburo\"},{\"id\":\"blk-fc8956e4-5f17-4e53-8fdf-77ba85d14b39\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Close views of hippos and crocodiles\"},{\"id\":\"blk-0048854e-cd5e-459c-b3b2-eaa37896d103\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent for bird photography\"}],\"wildlife\":[{\"id\":\"blk-b6dc692c-718d-4ea0-be36-003ac1691e8b\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Notable mammals include:\"},{\"id\":\"blk-99758b86-919b-4466-bdfc-6293e35e7d9f\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Zebras (very common and easily seen)\"},{\"id\":\"blk-2b2b1d6a-70d5-492a-aae9-2f891ccf0e43\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Impalas (only park in Uganda where they occur naturally)\"},{\"id\":\"blk-7fae44fa-1541-49c8-a69b-bbc5215570af\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Elands (largest antelope in Africa)\"},{\"id\":\"blk-ff699375-b5a1-4b22-a120-91b99e878042\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Topis\"},{\"id\":\"blk-b1db4f50-c7c9-4417-b439-64a5d7663622\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Bushbucks\"},{\"id\":\"blk-7405bacb-eb46-42c2-9c11-f4511736fadc\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Waterbucks\"},{\"id\":\"blk-20759060-fc6f-49e1-9175-b93287cabc46\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Buffaloes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-f87d94ce-549f-42e1-80a0-44df882a6360\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Warthogs\"},{\"id\":\"blk-f5959937-26f2-4459-8190-13745ed65eee\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Hippos\"},{\"id\":\"blk-ca744b68-7d39-4f5a-9d03-cf54734f8c5c\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Leopards (present but shy and mostly nocturnal)\"}],\"geography\":[],\"practical\":[],\"accommodation\":[],\"extras\":[]}', 0, 'Lake Mburo National Park is one of Uganda’s smallest but most diverse savannah parks, known for its rich wildlife, scenic landscapes, and wide range of visitor activities. It offers a compact yet rewarding safari experience and is especially suitable for short trips, stopovers, and travelers who want close wildlife encounters without long travel times.\r\n\r\n[[image:block-blk-0eac5c76-fef3-41b3-b91f-90ef3ffd20c9|]]', '## Game Drives\r\n\r\nMorning, afternoon, and night drives\r\n\r\nGood road network for viewing zebras and antelopes\r\n\r\nNight drives allow chances to see nocturnal animals\r\n\r\n## Boat Safaris\r\n\r\nConducted on Lake Mburo\r\n\r\nClose views of hippos and crocodiles\r\n\r\nExcellent for bird photography', '## Notable mammals include:\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Zebras (very common and easily seen)\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Impalas (only park in Uganda where they occur naturally)\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Elands (largest antelope in Africa)\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Topis\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Bushbucks\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Waterbucks\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Buffaloes\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Warthogs\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Hippos\r\n\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Leopards (present but shy and mostly nocturnal)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/featured/2FmwEtb1JqU9zR59tjmw6wFu2Qti4a4JoM7H4MJC.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'km²', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/yzE3Zds4eGKYhHF1x5z5AY2BXaMwx2m5z7DKF4i4.jpg', 1, 1, 5, '2026-02-13 11:54:54', '2026-03-11 21:53:15', NULL, '2026-03-11 21:53:15'),
(29, 3, NULL, 'City / Arrival', 'Entebbe', 'entebbe', NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'km²', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2026-02-19 06:32:10', '2026-03-04 04:51:43', NULL, NULL),
(30, 3, NULL, 'National Park', 'Mgahinga Gorilla National Park', 'mgahinga-gorilla-national-park', 'Nestled in the far southwestern corner of Uganda, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park is a breathtaking destination where dramatic volcanic landscapes meet rare wildlife encounters.', '{\"overview\":[{\"id\":\"blk-66261d9e-f341-48fd-8927-aa12b1738182\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Mgahinga Gorilla National Park  Uganda\\u2019s Hidden Treasure of Volcanoes and Gorillas\"},{\"id\":\"blk-a9fd3fd5-588f-41df-a4fc-e7ed9c1b8c2a\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nestled in the far southwestern corner of Uganda, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park is a breathtaking destination where dramatic volcanic landscapes meet rare wildlife encounters. As part of the greater Virunga Conservation Area shared with Rwanda and the Democratic Republic of Congo, the park offers an intimate and exclusive safari experience away from large crowds.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-4e906bc6-f0f8-4168-b417-4872a3167d42\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Famous for its endangered mountain gorillas and golden monkeys, Mgahinga is Uganda\\u2019s smallest national park, yet one of its most unique. The park is dominated by three extinct volcanoes\\u2014Mount Muhabura, Mount Gahinga, and Mount Sabyinyo creating a stunning backdrop of mist-covered peaks, bamboo forests, and rich biodiversity.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-085ea803-1a56-42d5-8e75-c3ac4e983a75\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ideal for adventure seekers, nature lovers, and primate enthusiasts, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park offers a rare opportunity to explore untouched wilderness while engaging in life-changing wildlife encounters.\"}],\"activities\":[{\"id\":\"blk-bde55848-e3d1-4a96-bee2-1267e4a7839f\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Top Activities in Mgahinga Gorilla National Park\"},{\"id\":\"blk-7a13af20-b93f-4a22-bc75-fa0b899716fb\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"1. Gorilla Trekking\"},{\"id\":\"blk-c77f0cc7-08b4-47d2-9991-2915c767e58d\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Gorilla trekking is the park\\u2019s flagship activity and one of the most unforgettable wildlife experiences in the world. Visitors hike through dense forests in search of a habituated gorilla family, guided by experienced rangers. Once located, you spend one magical hour observing these gentle giants in their natural habitat watching them feed, play, and interact. The experience is both thrilling and deeply emotional.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-6de82dde-f38d-4c30-95ab-532766d4b188\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"2. Golden Monkey Tracking\"},{\"id\":\"blk-9a77235c-34a2-4d8a-a57a-aa45bb9da8e2\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mgahinga is one of the few places in the world where you can track the rare and endangered golden monkeys. These playful primates inhabit the bamboo forests and are known for their speed and vibrant golden-orange fur. The tracking experience is less strenuous than gorilla trekking but equally rewarding.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-4d4ae8d3-d6f4-420d-840c-5b9b18dcb7fa\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"3. Volcano Hiking (Virunga Mountains)\"},{\"id\":\"blk-3725aa05-1d00-4420-a0d5-ee3c9ca3d67c\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For adventure lovers, Mgahinga offers incredible hiking opportunities across its three volcanoes: \\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Sabyinyo (where Uganda, Rwanda, and Congo meet)\\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Gahinga\\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Muhabura\\nEach hike provides breathtaking views, diverse vegetation zones, and a sense of achievement. The hikes range from moderate to challenging, making them suitable for different fitness levels.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-c0af826c-fdcc-40a1-a2a5-8d894c2d97ed\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"4. Batwa Cultural Experience\"},{\"id\":\"blk-a1c89eb0-c6a9-454b-8294-9182a4c507c1\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Batwa Trail offers a unique cultural encounter with the indigenous Batwa people, the original forest dwellers of the region. Visitors learn about their traditional hunting techniques, survival skills, and deep connection to the forest. This experience adds a meaningful cultural dimension to your safari.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-76c5a772-b064-4fa2-b0bd-a4bbbcf46a36\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"5. Nature Walks\"},{\"id\":\"blk-2849cc88-5732-4429-addc-f7476f4134fd\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Guided nature walks allow visitors to explore the park at a slower pace, discovering its flora, birdlife, and smaller wildlife species. These walks provide a deeper understanding of the park\\u2019s ecosystems and are perfect for those seeking a relaxed experience\"},{\"id\":\"blk-dad57b6a-186d-4fc7-b637-70f0869b7cd2\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"6. Bird Watching\"},{\"id\":\"blk-9eaac684-cba5-44b3-98e8-5d5bace2eddd\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mgahinga is a birding paradise, especially for Albertine Rift endemics. Bird enthusiasts can spot rare species within the forest and bamboo zones, making it a rewarding destination for both amateur and experienced birders.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-83fbae6a-ba16-42b5-a0f6-52cefb067c52\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"7. Photography & Scenic Viewing\"},{\"id\":\"blk-886e0d32-c8c8-41b3-bb61-c88ac34dd8b3\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"With its dramatic volcanic scenery, misty forests, and diverse wildlife, Mgahinga offers endless opportunities for photography. From sunrise over the Virunga Mountains to close encounters with primates, every moment is picture-perfect.\"}],\"wildlife\":[{\"id\":\"blk-668fb171-de3f-4db3-8622-5eb3bdbc8fb4\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"text\":\"Wildlife in Mgahinga Gorilla National Park\"},{\"id\":\"blk-5f18d55a-9dc1-4362-914a-78852167ce50\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"1. Mountain Gorillas\"},{\"id\":\"blk-2986abed-2ac7-4204-a84a-166dbc2ff8d4\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The park is home to a habituated gorilla family, offering visitors a rare chance to observe these critically endangered primates in their natural environment. Their human-like behavior and social structure make the experience deeply moving\"},{\"id\":\"blk-75143cd7-a6ac-42e5-8e67-4bf51c9749a6\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"2. Golden Monkeys\"},{\"id\":\"blk-bc165fa5-073f-48d3-8b6d-363210e3522c\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"These rare primates are unique to the Virunga region and are known for their striking golden fur and energetic movements. They are often seen jumping through bamboo forests in large groups.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-5ae20430-e9e9-4645-a5d5-1af311206e15\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"3. Forest Elephants\"},{\"id\":\"blk-137aaab6-8da7-440b-9ca3-1d6ac65fae8c\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Although rarely seen due to their shy nature, forest elephants inhabit the park. They are smaller than savannah elephants and adapted to forest life.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-a6add357-e935-4251-8645-5edcf4908f04\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"4. Buffaloes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-0f19f027-e03d-4416-be8c-7ea55f9d78e5\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"African buffaloes can be found within the park, often moving through forest clearings and lower vegetation zones.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-c2ff0a52-cfc6-4f74-a62d-b6397d995ed8\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"5. Bushbucks and Other Antelopes\"},{\"id\":\"blk-85413fb5-6158-4597-8e8b-bd9a85ffef8f\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Various antelope species such as bushbucks thrive in the park\\u2019s forested environment, contributing to its rich biodiversity\"},{\"id\":\"blk-b0fff51b-b9f8-42c2-9400-cb494f3bf89b\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"6. Bird Species\"},{\"id\":\"blk-6f2f75e1-05de-44b3-a380-f8b89bd39553\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mgahinga hosts numerous bird species, including Albertine Rift endemics, making it a hotspot for birdwatching enthusiasts\"}],\"geography\":[],\"practical\":[],\"accommodation\":[],\"extras\":[{\"id\":\"blk-0c4a5126-0530-4809-8e16-75471e6bd938\",\"type\":\"subheading\",\"text\":\"Why Mgahinga is Special\"},{\"id\":\"blk-b7567382-b8e4-4492-ad29-fc554dce63b1\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"What truly sets Mgahinga Gorilla National Park apart is its exclusive, crowd-free safari experience, offering travelers a more personal and intimate connection with nature. Unlike busier destinations, Mgahinga allows you to enjoy gorilla trekking in peaceful, untouched environment\\u2014making every encounter feel private, authentic, and deeply memorable.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-72f2e75d-d59d-4068-9f06-75856a52e524\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Uniquely, it is one of the few places in the world where you can track both mountain gorillas and golden monkeys in the same destination, giving you double the adventure in a single safari. This rare combination adds exceptional value and makes Mgahinga a top choice for travelers seeking something truly different.\"},{\"id\":\"blk-532ca9a6-6ba7-4d33-907c-4a8aa64e5f83\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Set against the dramatic backdrop of the Virunga volcanoes, the park delivers breathtaking scenery, rich biodiversity, and cultural depth through experiences like the Batwa trail. For clients looking for a safari that goes beyond the ordinary less crowded, more immersive, and incredibly rewarding\\u2014Mgahinga Gorilla National Park stands out as a hidden gem and a premium primate destination in Uganda.\"}]}', 0, '## Mgahinga Gorilla National Park  Uganda’s Hidden Treasure of Volcanoes and Gorillas\r\n\r\nNestled in the far southwestern corner of Uganda, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park is a breathtaking destination where dramatic volcanic landscapes meet rare wildlife encounters. As part of the greater Virunga Conservation Area shared with Rwanda and the Democratic Republic of Congo, the park offers an intimate and exclusive safari experience away from large crowds.\r\n\r\nFamous for its endangered mountain gorillas and golden monkeys, Mgahinga is Uganda’s smallest national park, yet one of its most unique. The park is dominated by three extinct volcanoes—Mount Muhabura, Mount Gahinga, and Mount Sabyinyo creating a stunning backdrop of mist-covered peaks, bamboo forests, and rich biodiversity.\r\n\r\nIdeal for adventure seekers, nature lovers, and primate enthusiasts, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park offers a rare opportunity to explore untouched wilderness while engaging in life-changing wildlife encounters.', '## Top Activities in Mgahinga Gorilla National Park\r\n\r\n## 1. Gorilla Trekking\r\n\r\nGorilla trekking is the park’s flagship activity and one of the most unforgettable wildlife experiences in the world. Visitors hike through dense forests in search of a habituated gorilla family, guided by experienced rangers. Once located, you spend one magical hour observing these gentle giants in their natural habitat watching them feed, play, and interact. The experience is both thrilling and deeply emotional.\r\n\r\n## 2. Golden Monkey Tracking\r\n\r\nMgahinga is one of the few places in the world where you can track the rare and endangered golden monkeys. These playful primates inhabit the bamboo forests and are known for their speed and vibrant golden-orange fur. The tracking experience is less strenuous than gorilla trekking but equally rewarding.\r\n\r\n## 3. Volcano Hiking (Virunga Mountains)\r\n\r\nFor adventure lovers, Mgahinga offers incredible hiking opportunities across its three volcanoes: \r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Sabyinyo (where Uganda, Rwanda, and Congo meet)\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Gahinga\r\n[[icon:fas fa-check-circle]] Mount Muhabura\r\nEach hike provides breathtaking views, diverse vegetation zones, and a sense of achievement. The hikes range from moderate to challenging, making them suitable for different fitness levels.\r\n\r\n## 4. Batwa Cultural Experience\r\n\r\nThe Batwa Trail offers a unique cultural encounter with the indigenous Batwa people, the original forest dwellers of the region. Visitors learn about their traditional hunting techniques, survival skills, and deep connection to the forest. This experience adds a meaningful cultural dimension to your safari.\r\n\r\n## 5. Nature Walks\r\n\r\nGuided nature walks allow visitors to explore the park at a slower pace, discovering its flora, birdlife, and smaller wildlife species. These walks provide a deeper understanding of the park’s ecosystems and are perfect for those seeking a relaxed experience\r\n\r\n## 6. Bird Watching\r\n\r\nMgahinga is a birding paradise, especially for Albertine Rift endemics. Bird enthusiasts can spot rare species within the forest and bamboo zones, making it a rewarding destination for both amateur and experienced birders.\r\n\r\n## 7. Photography & Scenic Viewing\r\n\r\nWith its dramatic volcanic scenery, misty forests, and diverse wildlife, Mgahinga offers endless opportunities for photography. From sunrise over the Virunga Mountains to close encounters with primates, every moment is picture-perfect.', '# Wildlife in Mgahinga Gorilla National Park\r\n\r\n1. Mountain Gorillas\r\n\r\nThe park is home to a habituated gorilla family, offering visitors a rare chance to observe these critically endangered primates in their natural environment. Their human-like behavior and social structure make the experience deeply moving\r\n\r\n## 2. Golden Monkeys\r\n\r\nThese rare primates are unique to the Virunga region and are known for their striking golden fur and energetic movements. They are often seen jumping through bamboo forests in large groups.\r\n\r\n## 3. Forest Elephants\r\n\r\nAlthough rarely seen due to their shy nature, forest elephants inhabit the park. They are smaller than savannah elephants and adapted to forest life.\r\n\r\n## 4. Buffaloes\r\n\r\nAfrican buffaloes can be found within the park, often moving through forest clearings and lower vegetation zones.\r\n\r\n## 5. Bushbucks and Other Antelopes\r\n\r\nVarious antelope species such as bushbucks thrive in the park’s forested environment, contributing to its rich biodiversity\r\n\r\n## 6. Bird Species\r\n\r\nMgahinga hosts numerous bird species, including Albertine Rift endemics, making it a hotspot for birdwatching enthusiasts', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '## Why Mgahinga is Special\r\n\r\nWhat truly sets Mgahinga Gorilla National Park apart is its exclusive, crowd-free safari experience, offering travelers a more personal and intimate connection with nature. Unlike busier destinations, Mgahinga allows you to enjoy gorilla trekking in peaceful, untouched environment—making every encounter feel private, authentic, and deeply memorable.\r\n\r\nUniquely, it is one of the few places in the world where you can track both mountain gorillas and golden monkeys in the same destination, giving you double the adventure in a single safari. This rare combination adds exceptional value and makes Mgahinga a top choice for travelers seeking something truly different.\r\n\r\nSet against the dramatic backdrop of the Virunga volcanoes, the park delivers breathtaking scenery, rich biodiversity, and cultural depth through experiences like the Batwa trail. For clients looking for a safari that goes beyond the ordinary less crowded, more immersive, and incredibly rewarding—Mgahinga Gorilla National Park stands out as a hidden gem and a premium primate destination in Uganda.', 'Mgahinga Gorilla National Park – Gorilla Trekking Safari', 'Discover Mgahinga Gorilla National Park gorilla trekking, golden monkeys, and volcanic landscapes in Uganda’s most scenic and uncrowded safari destination.', 'Mgahinga Gorilla Trekking, Mgahinga Gorilla National Park', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/featured/sg9d4Cft2oyg1ipfy8UVQftN2tdhqbqu8hGRlx4D.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'km²', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'destinations/fI4Fie1Vmo91lo8eNz5JWa7AJYZeorQEAzeTlrRD.jpg', 1, 1, 0, '2026-04-02 19:43:10', '2026-04-08 23:13:08', NULL, '2026-04-08 23:13:08');

